<recipe>
<title>
Asian Quinoa Chopped Salad with Asian Honey Mustard Dressing
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 15 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: quinoa
SERVINGS: 3 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="0.5 C ">Mayonnaise</ingredient><ingredient amount="3.0 t ">Honey</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 t ">Rice</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 s ">Mus</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
For the dressing, whisk together mayonnaise, rice wine vinegar, mustard, horseradish, and sesame oil until well-combined.
Cover, and chill dressing until ready to use.
For the salad, add all of the salad ingredients to a large bowl (or individual bowls if desired).
Serve with the dressing and garnished with slivered almonds and chow mein noodles.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>